# 1\. Purpose

The main purpose of the app is to create a fun and exciting virtual pet that you will be able to feed, play with and clean. The target audience for the app is children and teenagers but it is not limited to adults. The app gives you a daily hobby of you taking care of your virtual pet each and every day, making sure if your pet is clean, if its hunger or not and playing with it when it needs a play buddy.

## General design

The application is user friendly and it accommodates all age groups. The pictures are very attractive and they catch the user’s attention within the first glimpse. The design is not that colourful but it has some colours that make it pop

## Intuitive design

The application is not complicated at all it only has one button on the first page which while move you to the second page. Once you get to the second the application consists of 3 buttons, the feed button, clean button and play button. The application also has three text views which are the feed text view, clean text view and play text button. The design accommodates all age groups and it’s simple to understand.

## Content prioritisation

The users can easily understand what is expected from them. The application consists of all the necessary interface elements.

## Legible text

The font used is clear and big enough. Most off the font in the application is in bold and italics. The italic font is used to give the application a beautiful and fun appearance. The buttons are all in clear white font and the font size is clear enough.

## Make interface elements clearly visible

All the components on the screen are visible and large enough. There’s enough space between all the buttons and text views. The application has zero percent crowding.

## Hand position controls

The buttons are set in a way that they are easy to use and won’t cause any strain to the hands. The buttons are not separated far away from each other and are put in a way that the app can be used comfortably.

## Images

I choose this pictures because they have a greeting appearance and they make the user to want to spend more time on the application.

# 5\. Code

//code for the first page

class MainActivity : AppCompatActivity() {

override fun onCreate(savedInstanceState: Bundle?) {

super.onCreate(savedInstanceState)

setContentView(R.layout.activity_main)

//Button to navigate to the second page

val startButton = findViewById&lt;Button&gt;(R.id.startButton)

startButton.setOnClickListener {

val intent = Intent(this,MainActivity2::class.java)

startActivity(intent)

}

}}

//code for the second page:

class MainActivity2 : AppCompatActivity() {

override fun onCreate(savedInstanceState: Bundle?) {

super.onCreate(savedInstanceState)

setContentView(R.layout.activity_main2)

// Declerations

val petImageView = findViewById&lt;ImageView&gt;(R.id.petImageView)

val feedButton = findViewById&lt;Button&gt;(R.id.feedButton)

val cleanButton = findViewById&lt;Button&gt;(R.id.cleanButton)

val playButton = findViewById&lt;Button&gt;(R.id.playButton)

val tomTextView = findViewById&lt;TextView&gt;(R.id.tomTextView)

tomTextView.text = "Please feed me"

//change the pets image to match feed action icon

feedButton.setOnClickListener {

petImageView.setImageResource(R.drawable.image2)

//update the feed comment

tomTextView.text = "thank_you for feeding me,please clean me"

}

//change the pets image to match clean action icon

cleanButton.setOnClickListener {

petImageView.setImageResource(R.drawable.image4)

//update the clean comment

tomTextView.text = "thanks for cleaning me i fell so good,please play with me"

}

//change the pets image to match play action icon

playButton.setOnClickListener {

petImageView.setImageResource(R.drawable.image3)

//update the play comment

tomTextView.text = "it was nice playing with you"

}

}

}
